<div class="basictext">

	<div class="headtext">
	<a href="/recipe/Smothered_Chicken">Smothered Chicken + Barley</a>
	</div>

	<div class="basictext">
	Submitted by: carrien<br>
	Date: 2004-08-30<br>
	<br>
	</div>
<div class="recipetable" id="limitwidth">
<div class="ingredienttext">
<b>Ingredients:</b><br>1 t ground cumin<br />
1/2 t chili powder<br />
1/2 t salt<br />
1/2 t ground cinnamon<br />
1/8 t garlic powder<br />
1/8 t pepper<br />
6 chicken thighs<br />
4 T olive oil, divided<br />
1 1/2 c chopped onions<br />
1 c chopped red pepper<br />
1 T soy sauce<br />
3 1/2 c chicken broth<br />
1 1/4 c uncooked barley<br />
14.5 oz can of tomatoes, drained and chopped<br />
1 bunch green onions, chopped</div><br><br>
<div class="instructiontext">
<b>Instructions</b><br>
Combine the first six ingredients in a small bowl and rub the chicken with half the resulting spice mixture.  Brown chicken in 2 T oil in skillet over medium high heat.  Remove as it browns to baking pan.<br>
<br>
Add remaining oil to skillet.  Sauté onion and pepper a few minutes.  Add soy sauce and continue cooking a few more minutes.  Add broth, barley, tomatoes, and remaining spice mixture.  Bring to boil.  Pour mixture over chicken in baking pan.  Cover and bake 1 hour at 350°F.<br>
<br>
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.  Top with sliced green onions.
</div>
</div>
